  "prompt": "What is the most cheapest university in ontario?",
  "response": "The cost of attending a university in Ontario can vary based on factors such as the program, residency status (domestic or international), and additional fees. However, if you're looking for the most affordable options, here are a few universities in Ontario that are generally considered cost-effective for domestic students:\n\n### 1. **Toronto Metropolitan University (TMU)** \n   - Formerly Ryerson University, TMU offers competitive tuition fees, especially for programs in arts and humanities.\n\n### 2. **University of Guelph**\n   - Known for its agriculture and veterinary programs, Guelph offers relatively affordable tuition for domestic students.\n\n### 3. **Lakehead University**\n   - Located in Thunder Bay and Orillia, Lakehead is one of the most budget-friendly options in Ontario, particularly for smaller class sizes and lower living costs.\n\n### 4. **Nipissing University**\n   - Situated in North Bay, Nipissing is another affordable choice, especially for education and arts programs.\n\n### 5. **Algoma University**\n   - Located in Sault Ste. Marie, Algoma is one of the cheapest universities in Ontario, with lower tuition fees and a small campus environment.\n\n### Notes:\n- **Domestic vs. International Fees:** Tuition for international students is significantly higher than for domestic students.\n- **Additional Costs:** Remember to account for living expenses, textbooks, and other fees, which can vary by location.\n- **Scholarships and Financial Aid:** Many universities offer scholarships and bursaries to help reduce costs.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, visit the official websites of these universities or consult the **Ontario Universities' Application Centre (OUAC)**.",
